author: Megan Crepeau
title: 5 seriously injured in NW Side crash
text:
One person is in custody after a crash in Cragin that left five people in serious-to-critical condition, police and fire officials said.
At about 2:15 a.m., two cars were traveling southbound on Cicero Avenue near Armitage Avenue when one hit the other and both cars crashed, said Chicago police spokeswoman Officer Amina Greer. The driver of one car was taken into custody.
No information was available about the ages or genders of the people who were injured, but all were adults, said Chicago Fire Department Deputy District Chief Jeff Lyle.
Three people went to Stroger Hospital and two went to Mount Sinai Hospital, Lyle said.
 Chicago Police Department
